menuconfig IOLINKI_MASTER
    bool "IO-Link Master Stack"
    default y
    help
      Enable the iolinki IO-Link Master Stack. This module implements the
      master-side IO-Link Data Link Layer, ISDU engine, parameter/data-storage
      handling and SIO fallback, driving a device through a hardware-agnostic
      PHY abstraction (iolink_phy_api_t). It reuses the shared frame/CRC helper
      sources and public <iolinki/*.h> headers from the iolinki device stack,
      which must be present in the same west workspace (see west.yml).

if IOLINKI_MASTER

config IOLINKI_MASTER_CONTROLLER
    bool "Multi-port master controller helpers"
    default y
    help
      Build the multi-port controller layer (iolink_master_controller_*), which
      manages an array of ports from a single tick/scheduling entry point. The
      controller sources are always compiled with the master library; this
      symbol is provided so applications can gate controller-only code.

endif # IOLINKI_MASTER
